msgctxt "talk01"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.so>HA!<3.pa> Let me guess...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"You caught wind of the great Dr. Calip's\n"
"groundbreaking research and just HAD to\n"
"meet him for yourself.<4.pa> Heh...\n"
"No?<5.pa> Don't tell me you've never even\n"
"HEARD of me!<6.pa> After I've dedicated my\n"
"life to researching the ancient shrines?!\n"
"<7.so>*sigh*<8.pa> Well, you'd better remember my\n"
"name, for it's not the last you'll hear\n"
"of it!\n"
"<9.so>And while I'm at it, it's \"DOCTOR Calip,\"\n"
"if you please. <10.pa>I didn't study my rear end\n"
"off to be called \"Mr. Calip.\"\n"
"<11.te_si>Everyone forgets I'm a doctor for some "
"reason...<12.ra><13.so><14.so><15.te_si>And since you asked, I'll inform "
"you that\n"
"I'm engaged in analyzing ancient texts.\n"
"I haven't time for idle chitchat.<16.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound2
#. 3: pause (longer)
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: raw
#. 6: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk03"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.so>You again?<3.pa> What now?<4.pa> You want to tag\n"
"along on my fieldwork?<5.ra>Well, I suppose it might do you some\n"
"good to see an expert at work.<6.pa> Just try\n"
"to stay out of my way."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (long)
#. 4: choice
msgctxt "talk06"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh, it's you. <2.pa>Can whatever it is wait?<3.pa>\n"
"I'm VERY busy deciphering these ancient\n"
"texts.<4.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound2
#. 3: sound
#. 4: choice
msgctxt "talk10"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.so>Soon, my long years of research will be\n"
"revealed...and all the world will hail it as\n"
"the discovery of the century!\n"
"<3.so>To prevent any undue attention, I haven't\n"
"even told my family about my work.\n"
"You understand, I'm sure.<4.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk11"
msgid ""
"<1.so>...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"These ancient writings are like a gauntlet\n"
"laid before us from long-dead\n"
"civilizations!\n"
"Or, if you prefer, they are love letters\n"
"meant for the eyes of all archaeologists\n"
"seduced by history.\n"
"Do you see what I mean?<2.pa> Either way,\n"
"it's a private matter between me and my\n"
"relics. <3.pa>There's no room for laypersons."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: pause (longer)
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: pause (short)
#. 6: pause (longer)
#. 7: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk12"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Did I...<2.pa>just hear you call me doctor?<3.pa>\n"
"As in,<4.pa> not merely Calip,<5.pa> but DOCTOR\n"
"Calip?<6.pa>\n"
"It rolled off your tongue so naturally.<7.pa>\n"
"It was downright salivary!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound2
#. 3: choice
msgctxt "talk13"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.so>Will you never cease pestering me?\n"
"And call me by my proper title: Dr. Calip.\n"
"The \"Dr.\" is important.\n"
"Anyway, I'm busy deciphering these\n"
"ancient texts. Can whatever you need\n"
"wait until later?<3.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk15"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Unusually sensible of you. <2.pa>But if you\n"
"have the wit to address me by my proper\n"
"title, perhaps I shouldn't be so surprised.\n"
"My work keeps me far too busy to sleep,\n"
"so you can rest in my bed over there if\n"
"you need."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: raw
#. 4: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk16"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I only do fieldwork at shrines and ruins\n"
"during the day.<2.pa> Why, you ask?<3.ra>Hmm, could it have something to "
"do\n"
"with the hordes of monsters roaming at\n"
"night? <4.pa>What an ignoramus..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: raw
#. 4: sound
#. 5: sound2
#. 6: pause (short)
#. 7: pause (longer)
#. 8: pause (longer)
#. 9: sound2
#. 10: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk17"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hrm...<2.pa> This changes things...<3.ra><4.so><5.so>Very well "
"then!<6.pa> I'm feeling charitable,\n"
"so I'll let a few things spill.<7.pa> This is just\n"
"between us, understand.\n"
"\"When a dark light resides in the cursed\n"
"statue's eyes, pierce its gaze to purge\n"
"the seal from the shrine.\"<8.pa>\n"
"<9.so>I'm still in the process of deciphering\n"
"that one, so I don't suppose there's\n"
"any harm in sharing it with you.\n"
"But see here, there are far too many\n"
"dangers lurking at this time of night for\n"
"me to stand around discussing this.\n"
"If you want to rest in my bed, you may.<10.pa>\n"
"I tend to be far too engrossed in my\n"
"work to sleep..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound2
#. 3: pause (long)
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: sound
#. 6: choice
msgctxt "talk18"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.so>For goodness' sake, can you not take\n"
"even the broadest hint?<3.pa> I'm busy!<4.pa> These\n"
"ancient texts won't decipher themselves!\n"
"<5.so>Times like these make me long to be\n"
"back in academia, where at least people\n"
"understood the value of solitude...<6.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: raw
msgctxt "talk20"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I don't mind a little rain, but the lightning\n"
"in Hyrule is alarmingly attracted to\n"
"anything metallic.\n"
"No, on days like this, it's best to shut\n"
"oneself in and wait for the rain to clear.<2.ra>If you must go "
"gallivanting across the\n"
"countryside, take care you don't get\n"
"struck, at least."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk21"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Today's research trip is on hold.\n"
"My glasses are unfortunately metallic,\n"
"so I must remain indoors at all costs!<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk22"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Monsters roam these parts after nightfall.<2.pa>\n"
"It's best to stay safely inside until dawn."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk23"
msgid ""
"Today's research trip is on hold.\n"
"<1.so>My glasses are unfortunately metallic...\n"
"In this weather, my life could be at risk!<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

